Runtime engine (not bundled, reached over PATH)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

symprint shells out to the Typst typesetting engine. Typst is NOT distributed
with this software; users install it themselves. Typst is licensed under the
Apache License 2.0 — https://github.com/typst/typst

On first render the Typst engine fetches the following Typst Universe package
into its own package cache (network required once; Phase 2 will vendor it):

  @preview/cmarker  — CommonMark → Typst, MIT — https://github.com/SabrinaJewson/cmarker.typ

The DIN 5008 letter geometry is informed by these open-source templates
(consulted as references; see docs/architecture.md):

  Sematre/typst-letter-pro            — MIT
  pascal-huber/typst-letter-template  — MIT
  classy-german-invoice               — MIT-0
